obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (10810)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent, application and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10810&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Lokpal and`
  line `Lokayuktas Act, 2013.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall apply to public servants in and outside India.`
  line
  line `(4) It shall come into force on such date ^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 16th January, 2014, vide notification No. S.O. 119 (E), dated 16th January, 2014, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (10811)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10811&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,—`
  line
  line `(a) 'bench" means a bench of the Lokpal;`
  line
  line `(b) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the Lokpal;`
  line
  line `(c) "competent authority", in relation to—`
  line
  line `(i) the Prime Minister, means the House of the People;`
  line
  line `(ii) a member of the Council of Ministers, means the Prime Minister;`
  line
  line `(iii) a member of Parliament other than a Minister, means—`
  line
  line `(A) in the case of a member of the Council of States, the Chairman of the Council;`
  line and
  line
  line `(B) in the case of a member of the House of the People, the Speaker of the House;`
  line
  line `(iv) an officer in the Ministry or Department of the Central Government, means the Minister`
  line `in charge of the Ministry or Department under which the officer is serving;`
  line
  line `(v) a chairperson or members of any body or Board or corporation or authority or company or`
  line `society or autonomous body (by whatever name called) established or constituted under any Act`
  line `of Parliament or wholly or partly financed by the Central Government or controlled by it, means`
  line `the Minister in charge of the administrative Ministry of such body or Board or corporation or`
  line `authority or company or society or autonomous body;`
  line
  line `(vi) an officer of any body or Board or corporation or authority or company or society or`
  line `autonomous body (by whatever name called) established or constituted under any Act of`
  line `Parliament or wholly or partly financed by the Central Government or controlled by it, means the`
  line `head of such body or Board or corporation or authority or company or society or autonomous`
  line body;
  line
  line `(vii) in any other case not falling under sub-clauses (i) to (vi) above, means such Department`
  line `or authority as the Central Government may, by notification, specify:`
  line
  line `Provided that if any person referred to in sub-clause (v) or sub-clause (vi) is also a member of`
  line `Parliament, then, the competent authority shall be—`
  line
  line `(A) in case such member is a member of the Council of States, the Chairman of the`
  line `Council; and`
  line
  line `(B) in case such member is a member of the House of the People, the Speaker of the`
  line House;
  line
  line `(d) "Central Vigilance Commission" means the Central Vigilance Commission constituted`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Central Vigilance Commission Act, 2003 (45 of 2003);`
  line
  line `(e) "complaint" means a complaint, made in such form as may be prescribed, alleging that a`
  line `public servant has committed an offence punishable under the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988`
  line `(49 of 1988);`
  line
  line `(f) "Delhi Special Police Establishment" means the Delhi Special Police Establishment`
  line `constituted under sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Delhi Special Police Establishment Act, 1946`
  line `(25 of 1946);`
  line
  line `(g) "investigation" means an investigation as defined under clause (h) of section 2 of the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974);`
  line
  line `(h) "Judicial" Member means a Judicial Member of the Lokpal;`
  line
  line `(i) "Lokpal" means the body established under section 3;`
  line
  line `(j) "Member" means a Member of the Lokpal;`
  line
  line `(k) "Minister" means a Union Minister but does not include the Prime Minister;`
  line
  line `(l) "notification" means notification published in the Official Gazette and the expression`
  line `notify shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(m) "preliminary inquiry" means an inquiry conducted under this Act;`
  line
  line `(n) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(o) "public servant" means a person referred to in clauses (a) to (h) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 14 but does not include a public servant in respect of whom the jurisdiction is exercisable`
  line `by any court or other authority under the Army Act, 1950 (45 of 1950), the Air Force Act, 1950`
  line `(46 of 1950), the Navy Act, 1957 (62 of 1957) and the Coast Guard Act, 1978 (30 of 1978) or the`
  line `procedure is applicable to such public servant under those Acts;`
  line
  line `(p) "regulations" means regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(q) "rules" means rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(r) "Schedule" means a Schedule appended to this Act;`
  line
  line `(s) "Special Court" means the court of a Special Judge appointed under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 3 of the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988 (49 of 1988).`
  line
  line `(2) The words and expressions used herein and not defined in this Act but defined in the Prevention`
  line `of Corruption Act, 1988 (49 of 1988), shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in that Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Any reference in this Act to any other Act or provision thereof which is not in force in any area to`
  line `which this Act applies shall be construed to have a reference to the corresponding Act or provision`
  line `thereof in force in such area.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (10812)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of Lokpal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10812&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) On and from the commencement of this Act, there shall be`
  line `established, for the purpose of this Act, a body to be called the "Lokpal".`
  line
  line `(2) The Lokpal shall consist of—`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairperson, who is or has been a Chief Justice of India or is or has been a Judge of the`
  line `Supreme Court or an eminent person who fulfills the eligibility specified in clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (3); and`
  line
  line `(b) such number of Members, not exceeding eight out of whom fifty per cent. shall be Judicial`
  line `Members:`
  line
  line `Provided that not less than fifty per cent. of the Members of the Lokpal shall be from amongst the`
  line `persons belonging to the Scheduled Castes, the Scheduled Tribes, Other Backward Classes,`
  line `Minorities and women.`
  line
  line `(3) A person shall be eligible to be appointed,—`
  line
  line `(a) as a Judicial Member if he is or has been a Judge of the Supreme Court or is or has been a`
  line `Chief Justice of a High Court;`
  line
  line `(b) as a Member other than a Judicial Member, if he is a person of impeccable integrity and`
  line `outstanding ability having special knowledge and expertise of not less than twenty-five years in the`
  line `matters relating to anti-corruption policy, public administration, vigilance, finance including`
  line `insurance and banking, law and management.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chairperson or a Member shall not be—`
  line
  line `(i) a member of Parliament or a member of the Legislature of any State or Union territory;`
  line
  line `(ii) a person convicted of any offence involving moral turptitude;`
  line
  line `(iii) a person of less than forty-five years of age, on the date of assuming office as the`
  line `Chairperson or Member, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(iv) a member of any Panchayat or Municipality;`
  line
  line `(v) a person who has been removed or dismissed from the service of the Union or a State,`
  line
  line `and shall not hold any office of trust or profit (other than his office as the Chairperson or a Member) or be`
  line `affiliated with any political party or carry on any business or practise any profession and, accordingly,`
  line `before he enters upon his office, a person appointed as the Chairperson or a Member, as the case may be,`
  line `shall, if—`
  line
  line `(a) he holds any office of trust or profit, resign from such office; or`
  line
  line `(b) he is carrying on any business, sever his connection with the conduct and management of such`
  line `business; or`
  line
  line `(c) he is practising any profession, cease to practise such profession.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (10813)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Appointment of Chairperson and Members on recommendations of Selection Committee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10813&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chairperson and Members shall be appointed by the President after obtaining the`
  line `recommendations of a Selection Committee consisting of--`
  line
  line `(a) the Prime Minister--Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) the Speaker of the House of the People--Member;`
  line
  line `(c) the Leader of Opposition in the House of the People--Member;`
  line
  line `(d) the Chief Justice of India or a Judge of the Supreme Court nominated by him--Member;`
  line
  line `(e) one eminent jurist, as recommended by the Chairperson and Members referred to in clauses`
  line `(a) to (d) above, to be nominated by the President--Member.`
  line
  line `(2) No appointment of a Chairperson or a Member shall be invalid merely by reason of any vacancy`
  line `in the Selection Committee.`
  line
  line `(3) The Selection Committee shall for the purposes of selecting the Chairperson and Members of the`
  line `Lokpal and for preparing a panel of persons to be considered for appointment as such, constitute a Search`
  line `Committee consisting of at least seven persons of standing and having special knowledge and expertise in`
  line `the matters relating to anti-corruption policy, public administration, vigilance, policy making, finance`
  line `including insurance and banking, law and management or in any other matter which, in the opinion of the`
  line `Selection Committee, may be useful in making the selection of the Chairperson and Members of the`
  line `Lokpal:`
  line
  line `Provided that not less than fifty per cent. of the members of the Search Committee shall be from`
  line `amongst the persons belonging to the Scheduled Castes, the Scheduled Tribes, Other Backward Classes,`
  line `Minorities and women:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Selection Committee may also consider any person other than the persons`
  line `recommended by the Search Committee.`
  line
  line `(4) The Selection Committee shall regulate its own procedure in a transparent manner for selecting`
  line `the Chairperson and Members of the Lokpal.`
  line
  line `(5) The term of the Search Committee referred to in sub-section (3), the fees and allowances payable`
  line `to its members and the manner of selection of panel of names shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (10814)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Filling of vacancies of Chairperson or Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10814&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The President shall take or cause to be taken`
  line `all necessary steps for the appointment of a new Chairperson and Members at least three months before`
  line `the expiry of the term of the Chairperson or Member, as the case may be, in accordance with the`
  line `procedure laid down in this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (10815)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Term of office of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10815&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson and every Member shall, on the`
  line `recommendations of the Selection Committee, be appointed by the President by warrant under his hand`
  line `and seal and hold office as such for a term of five years from the date on which he enters upon his office`
  line `or until he attains the age of seventy years, whichever is earlier:`
  line
  line `Provided that he may—`
  line
  line `(a) by writing under his hand addressed to the President, resign his office; or`
  line
  line `(b) be removed from his office in the manner provided in section 37.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (10816)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Salary, allowances and other conditions of service of Chairperson and Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10816&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The salary,`
  line `allowances and other conditions of service of—`
  line
  line `(i) the Chairperson shall be the same as those of the Chief Justice of India;`
  line
  line `(ii) other Members shall be the same as those of a Judge of the Supreme Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Chairperson or a Member is, at the time of his appointment, in receipt of`
  line `pension (other than disability pension) in respect of any previous service under the Government of`
  line `India or under the Government of a State, his salary in respect of service as the Chairperson or, as the`
  line `case may be, as a Member, be reduced—`
  line
  line `(a) by the amount of that pension; and`
  line
  line `(b) if he has, before such appointment, received, in lieu of a portion of the pension due to him`
  line `in respect of such previous service, the commuted value thereof, by the amount of that portion of`
  line `the pension:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the salary, allowances and pension payable to, and other conditions of`
  line `service of, the Chairperson or a Member shall not be varied to his disadvantage after his`
  line appointment.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (10817)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Restriction on employment by Chairperson and Members after ceasing to hold office.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10817&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `On ceasing to hold office, the Chairperson and every Member shall be ineligible for—`
  line
  line `(i) reappointment as the Chairperson or a Member of the Lokpal;`
  line
  line `(ii) any diplomatic assignment, appointment as administrator of a Union territory and such other`
  line `assignment or appointment which is required by law to be made by the President by warrant under his`
  line `hand and seal;`
  line
  line `(iii) further employment to any other office of profit under the Government of India or the`
  line `Government of a State;`
  line
  line `(iv) contesting any election of President or Vice-President or Member of either House of`
  line `Parliament or Member of either House of a State Legislature or Municipality or Panchayat within a`
  line `period of five years from the date of relinquishing the post.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), a Member shall be eligible to be appointed`
  line `as a Chairperson, if his total tenure as Member and Chairperson does not exceed five years.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this section, it is hereby clarified that where the Member is`
  line `appointed as the Chairperson, his term of office shall not be more than five years in aggregate as the`
  line `Member and the Chairperson.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (10818)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Member to act as Chairperson or to discharge his functions in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10818&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) In`
  line `the event of occurrence of any vacancy in the office of the Chairperson by reason of his death, resignation`
  line `or otherwise, the President may, by notification, authorise the senior-most Member to act as the`
  line `Chairperson until the appointment of a new Chairperson to fill such vacancy.`
  line
  line `(2) When the Chairperson is unable to discharge his functions owing to absence on leave or`
  line `otherwise, the senior-most Member available, as the President may, by notification, authorise in this`
  line `behalf, shall discharge the functions of the Chairperson until the date on which the Chairperson resumes`
  line `his duties.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (10819)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Secretary, other officers and staff of Lokpal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10819&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be a Secretary to the Lokpal in`
  line `the rank of Secretary to Government of India, who shall be appointed by the Chairperson from a panel of`
  line `names sent by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) There shall be a Director of Inquiry and a Director of Prosecution not below the rank of`
  line `Additional Secretary to the Government of India or equivalent, who shall be appointed by the Chairperson`
  line `from a panel of names sent by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) The appointment of officers and other staff of the Lokpal shall be made by the Chairperson or`
  line `such Member or officer of Lokpal as the Chairperson may direct:`
  line
  line `Provided that the President may by rule require that the appointment in respect of any post or posts as`
  line `may be specified in the rule, shall be made after consultation with the Union Public Service Commission.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the provisions of any law made by Parliament, the conditions of service of Secretary`
  line `and other officers and staff of the Lokpal shall be such as may be specified by regulations made by the`
  line `Lokpal for the purpose:`
  line
  line `Provided that the regulations made under this sub-section shall, so far as they relate to salaries,`
  line `allowances, leave or pensions, require the approval of the President.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (10820)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Inquiry Wing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10820&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in any law for the time being in force,`
  line `the Lokpal shall constitute an Inquiry Wing headed by the Director of Inquiry for the purpose of`
  line `conducting preliminary inquiry into any offence alleged to have been committed by a public servant`
  line `punishable under the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988 (49 of 1988):`
  line
  line `Provided that till such time the Inquiry Wing is constituted by the Lokpal, the Central Government`
  line `shall make available such number of officers and other staff from its Ministries or Departments, as may`
  line `be required by the Lokpal, for conducting preliminary inquiries under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of assisting the Lokpal in conducting a preliminary inquiry under this Act, the`
  line `officers of the Inquiry Wing not below the rank of the Under Secretary to the Government of India, shall`
  line `have the same powers as are conferred upon the Inquiry Wing of the Lokpal under section 27.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (10821)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Prosecution Wing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10821&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Lokpal shall, by notification, constitute a Prosecution Wing headed`
  line `by the Director of Prosecution for the purpose of prosecution of public servants in relation to any`
  line `complaint by the Lokpal under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that till such time the Prosecution Wing is constituted by the Lokpal, the Central`
  line `Government shall make available such number of officers and other staff from its Ministries or`
  line `Departments, as may be required by the Lokpal, for conducting prosecution under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director of Prosecution shall, after having been so directed by the Lokpal, file a case in`
  line `accordance with the findings of investigation report, before the Special Court and take all necessary steps`
  line `in respect of the prosecution of public servants in relation to any offence punishable under the Prevention`
  line `of Corruption Act, 1988 (49 of 1988).`
  line
  line `(3) The case under sub-section (2), shall be deemed to be a report, filed on completion of`
  line `investigation, referred to in section 173 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (10822)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Expenses of Lokpal to be charged on Consolidated Fund of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10822&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The administrative`
  line `expenses of the Lokpal, including all salaries, allowances and pensions payable to or in respect of the`
  line `Chairperson, Members or Secretary or other officers or staff of the Lokpal, shall be charged upon the`
  line `Consolidated Fund of India and any fees or other moneys taken by the Lokpal shall form part of that`
  line Fund.
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (10823)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Jurisdiction of Lokpal to include Prime Minister, Ministers, members of Parliament, Groups A, B, C and D officers and officials of Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10823&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the other`
  line `provisions of this Act, the Lokpal shall inquire or cause an inquiry to be conducted into any matter`
  line `involved in, or arising from, or connected with, any allegation of corruption made in a complaint in`
  line `respect of the following, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) any person who is or has been a Prime Minister:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Lokpal shall not inquire into any matter involved in, or arising from, or`
  line `connected with, any such allegation of corruption against the Prime Minister,—`
  line
  line `(i) in so far as it relates to international relations, external and internal security, public order,`
  line `atomic energy and space;`
  line
  line `(ii) unless a full bench of the Lokpal consisting of its Chairperson and all Members considers`
  line `the initiation of inquiry and at least two-thirds of its Members approves of such inquiry:`
  line
  line `Provided further that any such inquiry shall be held in camera and if the Lokpal comes to the`
  line `conclusion that the complaint deserves to be dismissed, the records of the inquiry shall not be`
  line `published or made available to anyone;`
  line
  line `(b) any person who is or has been a Minister of the Union;`
  line
  line `(c) any person who is or has been a member of either House of Parliament;`
  line
  line `(d) any Group 'A' or Group 'B' officer or equivalent or above, from amongst the public servants`
  line `defined in sub-clauses (i) and (ii) of clause (c) of section 2 of the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988`
  line `(49 of 1988) when serving or who has served, in connection with the affairs of the Union;`
  line
  line `(e) any Group 'C' or Group 'D' official or equivalent, from amongst the public servants defined in`
  line `sub-clauses (i) and (ii) of clause (c) of section 2 of the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988`
  line `(49 of 1988) when serving or who has served in connection with the affairs of the Union subject to`
  line `the provision of sub-section (1) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(f) any person who is or has been a chairperson or member or officer or employee in any body or`
  line `Board or corporation or authority or company or society or trust or autonomous body (by whatever`
  line `name called) established by an Act of Parliament or wholly or partly financed by the Central`
  line `Government or controlled by it:`
  line
  line `Provided that in respect of such officers referred to in clause (d) who have served in connection`
  line `with the affairs of the Union or in any body or Board or corporation or authority or company or`
  line `society or trust or autonomous body referred to in clause (e) but are working in connection with the`
  line `affairs of the State or in any body or Board or corporation or authority or company or society or trust`
  line `or autonomous body (by whatever name called) established by an Act of the State Legislature or`
  line `wholly or partly financed by the State Government or controlled by it, the Lokpal and the officers of`
  line `its Inquiry Wing or Prosecution Wing shall have jurisdiction under this Act in respect of such officers`
  line `only after obtaining the consent of the concerned State Government;`
  line
  line `(g) any person who is or has been a director, manager, secretary or other officer of every other`
  line `society or association of persons or trust (whether registered under any law for the time being in force`
  line `or not), by whatever name called, wholly or partly financed by the Government and the annual`
  line `income of which exceeds such amount as the Central Government may, by notification, specify;`
  line
  line `(h) any person who is or has been a director, manager, secretary or other officer of every other`
  line `society or association of persons or trust (whether registered under any law for the time being in force`
  line `or not) in receipt of any donation from any foreign source under the Foreign Contribution`
  line `(Regulation) Act, 2010 (42 of 2010) in excess of ten lakh rupees in a year or such higher amount as`
  line `the Central Government may, by notification, specify.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purpose of clauses (f) and (g), it is hereby clarified that any entity or`
  line `institution, by whatever name called, corporate, society, trust, association of persons, partnership, sole`
  line `proprietorship, limited liability partnership (whether registered under any law for the time being in force`
  line `or not), shall be the entities covered in those clauses:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person referred to in this clause shall be deemed to be a public servant under clause`
  line `(c) of section 2 of the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988 (49 of 1988) and the provisions of that Act`
  line `shall apply accordingly.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Lokpal shall not inquire into any`
  line `matter involved in, or arising from, or connected with, any such allegation of corruption against any`
  line `member of either House of Parliament in respect of anything said or a vote given by him in Parliament or`
  line `any committee thereof covered under the provisions contained in clause (2) of article 105 of the`
  line Constitution.
  line
  line `(3) The Lokpal may inquire into any act or conduct of any person other than those referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1), if such person is involved in the act of abetting, bribe giving or bribe taking or conspiracy`
  line `relating to any allegation of corruption under the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988 (49 of 1988) against`
  line `a person referred to in sub-section (1):`
  line
  line `Provided that no action under this section shall be taken in case of a person serving in connection`
  line `with the affairs of a State, without the consent of the State Government.`
  line
  line `(4) No matter in respect of which a complaint has been made to the Lokpal under this Act, shall be`
  line `referred for inquiry under the Commissions of Inquiry Act, 1952 (60 of 1952).`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that a complaint under this Act shall`
  line `only relate to a period during which the public servant was holding or serving in that capacity.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (10824)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Matters pending before any court or committee or authority for inquiry not to be affected.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10824&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `In case any matter or proceeding related to allegation of corruption under the Prevention`
  line `of Corruption Act, 1988 (49 of 1988) has been pending before any court or committee of either House of Parliament or before any other authority prior to commencement of this Act or prior to commencement`
  line `of any inquiry after the commencement of this Act, such matter or proceeding shall be continued before`
  line `such court, committee or authority.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (10825)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Constitution of benches of Lokpal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10825&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act,—`
  line
  line `(a) the jurisdiction of the Lokpal may be exercised by benches thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) a bench may be constituted by the Chairperson with two or more Members as the Chairperson`
  line `may deem fit;`
  line
  line `(c) every bench shall ordinarily consist of at least one Judicial Member;`
  line
  line `(d) where a bench consists of the Chairperson, such bench shall be presided over by the`
  line Chairperson;
  line
  line `(e) where a bench consists of a Judicial Member, and a non-Judicial Member, not being the`
  line `Chairperson, such bench shall be presided over by the Judicial Member;`
  line
  line `(f) the benches of the Lokpal shall ordinarily sit at New Delhi and at such other places as the`
  line `Lokpal may, by regulations, specify.`
  line
  line `(2) The Lokpal shall notify the areas in relation to which each bench of the Lokpal may exercise`
  line jurisdiction.
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the Chairperson shall have the power to`
  line `constitute or reconstitute benches from time to time.`
  line
  line `(4) If at any stage of the hearing of any case or matter it appears to the Chairperson or a Member that`
  line `the case or matter is of such nature that it ought to be heard by a bench consisting of three or more`
  line `Members, the case or matter may be transferred by the Chairperson or, as the case may be, referred to him`
  line `for transfer, to such bench as the Chairperson may deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (10826)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Distribution of business amongst benches.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10826&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Where benches are constituted, the Chairperson`
  line `may, from time to time, by notification, make provisions as to the distribution of the business of the`
  line `Lokpal amongst the benches and also provide for the matters which may be dealt with by each bench.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (10827)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Power of Chairperson to transfer cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10827&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `On an application for transfer made by the`
  line `complainant or the public servant, the Chairperson, after giving an opportunity of being heard to the`
  line `complainant or the public servant, as the case may be, may transfer any case pending before one bench for`
  line `disposal to any other bench.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (10828)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Decision to be by majority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10828&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `If the Members of a bench consisting of an even number of`
  line `Members differ in opinion on any point, they shall state the point or points on which they differ, and`
  line `make a reference to the Chairperson who shall either hear the point or points himself or refer the case for`
  line `hearing on such point or points by one or more of the other Members of the Lokpal and such point or`
  line `points shall be decided according to the opinion of the majority of the Members of the Lokpal who have`
  line `heard the case, including those who first heard it.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (10829)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Provisions relating to complaints and preliminary inquiry and investigation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10829&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Lokpal on receipt of a complaint, if it decides to proceed further, may order--`
  line
  line `(a) preliminary inquiry against any public servant by its Inquiry Wing or any agency (including`
  line `the Delhi Special Police Establishment) to ascertain whether there exists a prima facie case for`
  line `proceeding in the matter; or`
  line
  line `(b) investigation by any agency (including the Delhi Special Police Establishment) when there`
  line `exists a prima facie case:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Lokpal shall if it has decided to proceed with the preliminary inquiry, by a general`
  line `or special order, refer the complaints or a category of complaints or a complaint received by it in respect`
  line `of public servants belonging to Group A or Group B or Group C or Group D to the Central Vigilance Commission constituted under sub-section (1) of section 3 of the Central Vigilance Commission Act,`
  line `2003 (45 of 2003):`
  line
  line `Provided further that the Central Vigilance Commission in respect of complaints referred to it under`
  line `the first proviso, after making preliminary inquiry in respect of public servants belonging to Group A and`
  line `Group B, shall submit its report to the Lokpal in accordance with the provisions contained in sub-sections`
  line `(2) and (4) and in case of public servants belonging to Group C and Group D, the Commission shall`
  line `proceed in accordance with the provisions of the Central Vigilance Commission Act, 2003 (45 of 2003):`
  line
  line `Provided also that before ordering an investigation under clause (b), the Lokpal shall call for the`
  line `explanation of the public servant so as to determine whether there exists a prima facie case for`
  line `investigation:`
  line
  line `Provided also that the seeking of explanation from the public servant before an investigation shall not`
  line `interfere with the search and seizure, if any, required to be undertaken by any agency (including the Delhi`
  line `Special Police Establishment) under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) During the preliminary inquiry referred to in sub-section (1), the Inquiry Wing or any agency`
  line `(including the Delhi Special Police Establishment) shall conduct a preliminary inquiry and on the basis of`
  line `material, information and documents collected seek the comments on the allegations made in the`
  line `complaint from the public servant and the competent authority and after obtaining the comments of the`
  line `concerned public servant and the competent authority, submit, within sixty days from the date of receipt`
  line `of the reference, a report to the Lokpal.`
  line
  line `(3) A bench consisting of not less than three Members of the Lokpal shall consider every report`
  line `received under sub-section (2) from the Inquiry Wing or any agency (including the Delhi Special Police`
  line `Establishment), and after giving an opportunity of being heard to the public servant, decide whether there`
  line `exists a prima facie case, and proceed with one or more of the following actions, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) investigation by any agency or the Delhi Special Police Establishment, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(b) initiation of the departmental proceedings or any other appropriate action against the`
  line `concerned public servants by the competent authority;`
  line
  line `(c) closure of the proceedings against the public servant and to proceed against the complainant`
  line `under section 46.`
  line
  line `(4) Every preliminary inquiry referred to in sub-section (1) shall ordinarily be completed within a`
  line `period of ninety days and for reasons to be recorded in writing, within a further period of ninety days`
  line `from the date of receipt of the complaint.`
  line
  line `(5) In case the Lokpal decides to proceed to investigate into the complaint, it shall direct any agency`
  line `(including the Delhi Special Police Establishment) to carry out the investigation as expeditiously as`
  line `possible and complete the investigation within a period of six months from the date of its order:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Lokpal may extend the said period by a further period not exceeding of six months`
  line `at a time for the reasons to be recorded in writing.`
  line
  line `(6) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 173 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974), any agency (including the Delhi Special Police Establishment) shall, in respect of cases`
  line `referred to it by the Lokpal, submit the investigation report under that section to the court having`
  line `jurisdiction and forward a copy thereof to the Lokpal.`
  line
  line `(7) A bench consisting of not less than three Members of the Lokpal shall consider every report`
  line `received by it under sub-section (6) from any agency (including the Delhi Special Police Establishment)`
  line `and after obtaining the comments of the competent authority and the public servant may--`
  line
  line `(a) grant sanction to its Prosecution Wing or investigating agency to file charge-sheet or direct`
  line `the closure of report before the Special Court against the public servant;`
  line
  line `(b) direct the competent authority to initiate the departmental proceedings or any other`
  line `appropriate action against the concerned public servant.`
  line
  line `(8) The Lokpal may, after taking a decision under sub-section (7) on the filing of the charge-sheet,`
  line `direct its Prosecution Wing or any investigating agency (including the Delhi Special Police Establishment) to initiate prosecution in the Special Court in respect of the cases investigated by the`
  line agency.
  line
  line `(9) The Lokpal may, during the preliminary inquiry or the investigation, as the case may be, pass`
  line `appropriate orders for the safe custody of the documents relevant to the preliminary inquiry or, as the case`
  line `may be, investigation as it deems fit.`
  line
  line `(10) The website of the Lokpal shall, from time to time and in such manner as may be specified by`
  line `regulations, display to the public, the status of number of complaints pending before it or disposed of by`
  line it.
  line
  line `(11) The Lokpal may retain the original records and evidences which are likely to be required in the`
  line `process of preliminary inquiry or investigation or conduct of a case by it or by the Special Court.`
  line
  line `(12) Save as otherwise provided, the manner and procedure of conducting a preliminary inquiry or investigation (including such material and documents to be made available to the public servant) under`
  line `this Act, shall be such as may be specified by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (10830)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Persons likely to be prejudicially affected to be heard.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10830&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `If, at any stage of the proceeding, the`
  line Lokpal—
  line
  line `(a) considers it necessary to inquire into the conduct of any person other than the accused; or`
  line
  line `(b) is of opinion that the reputation of any person other than an accused is likely to be`
  line `prejudicially affected by the preliminary inquiry,`
  line
  line `the Lokpal shall give to that person a reasonable opportunity of being heard in the preliminary inquiry and`
  line `to produce evidence in his defence, consistent with the principles of natural justice.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (10831)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Lokpal may require any public servant or any other person to furnish information, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10831&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Subject to the provisions of this Act, for the purpose of any preliminary inquiry or investigation, the`
  line `Lokpal or the investigating agency, as the case may be, may require any public servant or any other`
  line `person who, in its opinion, is able to furnish information or produce documents relevant to such`
  line `preliminary inquiry or investigation, to furnish any such information or produce any such document`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (10832)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power of Lokpal to grant sanction for initiating prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10832&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in section 197 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) or section 6A of the Delhi`
  line `Special Police Establishment Act, 1946 (25 of 1946) or section 19 of the Prevention of Corruption Act,`
  line `1988 (49 of 1988), the Lokpal shall have the power to grant sanction for prosecution under clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (7) of section 20.`
  line
  line `(2) No prosecution under sub-section (1) shall be initiated against any public servant accused of any`
  line `offence alleged to have been committed by him while acting or purporting to act in the discharge of his`
  line `official duty, and no court shall take cognizance of such offence except with the previous sanction of the`
  line Lokpal.
  line
  line `(3) Nothing contained in sub-sections (1) and (2) shall apply in respect of the persons holding office`
  line `in pursuance of the provisions of the Constitution and in respect of which a procedure for removal of such`
  line `person has been specified therein.`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions contained in sub-sections (1), (2) and (3) shall be without prejudice to the`
  line `generality of the provisions contained in article 311 and sub-clause (c) of clause (3) of article 320 of the`
  line Constitution.
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (10833)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Action on investigation against public servant being Prime Minister, Ministers or members of Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10833&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Where, after the conclusion of the investigation, the findings of the Lokpal disclose the`
  line `commission of an offence under the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988 (49 of 1988) by a public servant`
  line `referred to in clause (a) or clause (b) or clause (c) of sub-section (1) of section 14, the Lokpal may file a`
  line `case in the Special Court and shall send a copy of the report together with its findings to the competent`
  line authority.
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (10834)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Supervisory powers of Lokpal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10834&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Lokpal shall, notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `section 4 of the Delhi Special Police Establishment Act, 1946 (25 of 1946) and section 8 of the Central`
  line `Vigilance Commission Act, 2003 (45 of 2003), have the powers of superintendence over, and to give`
  line `direction to the Delhi Special Police Establishment in respect of the matters referred by the Lokpal for`
  line `preliminary inquiry or investigation to the Delhi Special Police Establishment under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that while exercising powers of superintendence or giving direction under this sub-section,`
  line `the Lokpal shall not exercise powers in such a manner so as to require any agency (including the Delhi`
  line `Special Police Establishment) to whom the investigation has been given, to investigate and dispose of any`
  line `case in a particular manner.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Vigilance Commission shall send a statement, at such interval as the Lokpal may`
  line `direct, to the Lokpal in respect of action taken on complaints referred to it under the second proviso to`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 20 and on receipt of such statement, the Lokpal may issue guidelines for`
  line `effective and expeditious disposal of such cases.`
  line
  line `(3) Any officer of the Delhi Special Police Establishment investigating a case referred to it by the`
  line `Lokpal, shall not be transferred without the approval of the Lokpal.`
  line
  line `(4) The Delhi Special Police Establishment may, with the consent of the Lokpal, appoint a panel of`
  line `Advocates, other than the Government Advocates, for conducting the cases referred to it by the Lokpal.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government may from time to time make available such funds as may be required by`
  line `the Director of the Delhi Special Police Establishment for conducting effective investigation into the`
  line `matters referred to it by the Lokpal and the Director shall be responsible for the expenditure incurred in`
  line `conducting such investigation.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (10835)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Search and seizure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10835&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Lokpal has reason to believe that any document which, in its`
  line `opinion, shall be useful for, or relevant to, any investigation under this Act, are secreted in any place, it`
  line `may authorise any agency (including the Delhi Special Police Establishment) to whom the investigation`
  line `has been given to search for and to seize such documents.`
  line
  line `(2) If the Lokpal is satisfied that any document seized under sub-section (1) may be used as evidence`
  line `for the purpose of any investigation under this Act and that it shall be necessary to retain the document in`
  line `its custody or in the custody of such officer as may be authorised, it may so retain or direct such`
  line `authorised officer to retain such document till the completion of such investigation:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any document is required to be returned, the Lokpal or the authorised officer may`
  line `return the same after retaining copies of such document duly authenticated.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (10836)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Lokpal to have powers of civil court in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10836&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this`
  line `section, for the purpose of any preliminary inquiry, the Inquiry Wing of the Lokpal shall have all the`
  line `powers of a civil court, under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a suit in respect`
  line `of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(i) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(ii) requiring the discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(iii) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(iv) requisitioning any public record or copy thereof from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(v) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents:`
  line
  line `Provided that such commission, in case of a witness, shall be issued only where the witness, in`
  line `the opinion of the Lokpal, is not in a position to attend the proceeding before the Lokpal; and`
  line
  line `(vi) such other matters as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Any proceeding before the Lokpal shall be deemed to be a judicial proceeding within the meaning`
  line `of section 193 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (10837)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power of Lokpal to utilise services of officers of Central or State Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10837&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Lokpal may, for the purpose of conducting any preliminary inquiry or investigation, utilise the services of`
  line `any officer or organisation or investigating agency of the Central Government or any State Government,`
  line `as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of preliminary inquiry or investigating into any matter pertaining to such inquiry`
  line `or investigation, any officer or organisation or agency whose services are utilised under sub-section (1)`
  line `may, subject to the superintendence and direction of the Lokpal,—`
  line
  line `(a) summon and enforce the attendance of any person and examine him;`
  line
  line `(b) require the discovery and production of any document; and`
  line
  line `(c) requisition any public record or copy thereof from any office.`
  line
  line `(3) The officer or organisation or agency whose services are utilised under sub-section (2) shall`
  line `inquire or, as the case may be, investigate into any matter pertaining to the preliminary inquiry or`
  line `investigation and submit a report thereon to the Lokpal within such period as may be specified by it in`
  line `this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (10838)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Provisional attachment of assets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10838&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Lokpal or any officer authorised by it in this`
  line `behalf, has reason to believe, the reason for such belief to be recorded in writing, on the basis of material`
  line `in his possession, that—`
  line
  line `(a) any person is in possession of any proceeds of corruption;`
  line
  line `(b) such person is accused of having committed an offence relating to corruption; and`
  line
  line `(c) such proceeds of offence are likely to be concealed, transferred or dealt with in any manner`
  line `which may result in frustrating any proceedings relating to confiscation of such proceeds of offence,`
  line
  line `the Lokpal or the authorised officer may, by order in writing, provisionally attach such property for a`
  line `period not exceeding ninety days from the date of the order, in the manner provided in the Second`
  line `Schedule to the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961) and the Lokpal and the officer shall be deemed to be`
  line `an officer under sub-rule (e) of rule 1 of that Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) The Lokpal or the officer authorised in this behalf shall, immediately after attachment under`
  line `sub-section (1), forward a copy of the order, along with the material in his possession, referred to in that`
  line `sub-section, to the Special Court, in a sealed envelope, in the manner as may be prescribed and such`
  line `Court may extend the order of attachment and keep such material for such period as the Court may deem`
  line fit.
  line
  line `(3) Every order of attachment made under sub-section (1) shall cease to have effect after the expiry of`
  line `the period specified in that sub-section or after the expiry of the period as directed by the Special Court`
  line `under sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in this section shall prevent the person interested in the enjoyment of the immovable`
  line `property attached under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), from such enjoyment.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this sub-section, "person interested", in relation to any immovable`
  line `property, includes all persons claiming or entitled to claim any interest in the property.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (10839)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Confirmation of attachment of assets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10839&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Lokpal, when it provisionally attaches any`
  line `property under sub-section (1) of section 29 shall, within a period of thirty days of such attachment, direct`
  line `its Prosecution Wing to file an application stating the facts of such attachment before the Special Court`
  line `and make a prayer for confirmation of attachment of the property till completion of the proceedings`
  line `against the public servant in the Special Court.`
  line
  line `(2) The Special Court may, if it is of the opinion that the property provisionally attached had been`
  line `acquired through corrupt means, make an order for confirmation of attachment of such property till the`
  line `completion of the proceedings against the public servant in the Special Court.`
  line
  line `(3) If the public servant is subsequently acquitted of the charges framed against him, the property,`
  line `subject to the orders of the Special Court, shall be restored to the concerned public servant along with`
  line `benefits from such property as might have accrued during the period of attachment.`
  line
  line `(4) If the public servant is subsequently convicted of the charges of corruption, the proceeds relatable`
  line `to the offence under the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988 (49 of 1988) shall be confiscated and vest in`
  line `the Central Government free from any encumbrance or leasehold interest excluding any debt due to any`
  line `bank or financial institution.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purposes of this sub-section, the expressions "bank", "debt" and "financial`
  line `"institution" shall have the meanings respectively assigned to them in clauses (d), (g) and (h) of section 2`
  line `of the Recovery of Debts Due to Banks and Financial Institutions Act, 1993 (51 of 1993).`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (10840)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Confiscation of assets, proceeds, receipts and benefits arisen or procured by means of corruption in special circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10840&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to the provisions of sections 29 and 30,`
  line `where the Special Court, on the basis of prima facie evidence, has reason to believe or is satisfied that the`
  line `assets, proceeds, receipts and benefits, by whatever name called, have arisen or procured by means of`
  line `corruption by the public servant, it may authorise the confiscation of such assets, proceeds, receipts and`
  line `benefits till his acquittal.`
  line
  line `(2) Where an order of confiscation made under sub-section (1) is modified or annulled by the High`
  line `Court or where the public servant is acquitted by the Special Court, the assets, proceeds, receipts and`
  line `benefits, confiscated under sub-section (1) shall be returned to such public servant, and in case it is not`
  line `possible for any reason to return the assets, proceeds, receipts and benefits, such public servant shall be`
  line `paid the price thereof including the money so confiscated with interest at the rate of five per cent. per`
  line `annum thereon calculated from the date of confiscation`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (10841)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power of Lokpal to recommend transfer or suspension of public servant connected with allegation of corruption.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10841&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the Lokpal, while making a preliminary inquiry into allegations of`
  line `corruption, is prima facie satisfied, on the basis of evidence available,—`
  line
  line `(i) that the continuance of the public servant referred to in clause (d) or clause (e) or clause (f) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 14 in his post while conducting the preliminary inquiry is likely to affect`
  line `such preliminary inquiry adversely; or`
  line
  line `(ii) such public servant is likely to destroy or in any way tamper with the evidence or influence`
  line witnesses,
  line
  line `then, the Lokpal may recommend to the Central Government for transfer or suspension of such public`
  line `servant from the post held by him till such period as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government shall ordinarily accept the recommendation of the Lokpal made under`
  line `sub-section (1), except for the reasons to be recorded in writing in a case where it is not feasible to do so`
  line `for administrative reasons`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (10842)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Power of Lokpal to give directions to prevent destruction of records during preliminary inquiry.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10842&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The Lokpal may, in the discharge of its functions under this Act, issue appropriate directions`
  line `to a public servant entrusted with the preparation or custody of any document or record—`
  line
  line `(a) to protect such document or record from destruction or damage; or`
  line
  line `(b) to prevent the public servant from altering or secreting such document or record; or`
  line
  line `(c) to prevent the public servant from transferring or alienating any assets allegedly acquired by`
  line `him through corrupt means.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (10843)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Power to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10843&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `The Lokpal may, by general or special order in writing, and subject to such`
  line `conditions and limitations as may be specified therein, direct that any administrative or financial power`
  line `conferred on it may also be exercised or discharged by such of its Members or officers or employees as`
  line `may be specified in the order.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (10844)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Special Courts to be constituted by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10844&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall`
  line `constitute such number of Special Courts, as recommended by the Lokpal, to hear and decide the cases`
  line `arising out of the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988 (49 of 1988) or under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Special Courts constituted under sub-section (1) shall ensure completion of each trial within a`
  line `period of one year from the date of filing of the case in the Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case the trial cannot be completed within a period of one year, the Special Court shall`
  line `record reasons therefore and complete the trial within a further period of not more than three months or`
  line `such further periods not exceeding three months each, for reasons to be recorded in writing before the end`
  line `of each such three months period, but not exceeding a total period of two years.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (10845)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Letter of request to a contracting State in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10845&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in this Act or the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) if, in the course of an`
  line `preliminary inquiry or investigation into an offence or other proceeding under this Act, an application is`
  line `made to a Special Court by an officer of the Lokpal authorised in this behalf that any evidence is required`
  line `in connection with the preliminary inquiry or investigation into an offence or proceeding under this Act`
  line `and he is of the opinion that such evidence may be available in any place in a contracting State, and the`
  line `Special Court, on being satisfied that such evidence is required in connection with the preliminary inquiry`
  line `or investigation into an offence or proceeding under this Act, may issue a letter of request to a court or an`
  line `authority in the contracting State competent to deal with such request to—`
  line
  line `(i) examine the facts and circumstances of the case;`
  line
  line `(ii) take such steps as the Special Court may specify in such letter of request; and`
  line
  line `(iii) forward all the evidence so taken or collected to the Special Court issuing such letter of`
  line request.
  line
  line `(2) The letter of request shall be transmitted in such manner as the Central Government may prescribe`
  line `in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) Every statement recorded or document or thing received under sub-section (1) shall be deemed to`
  line `be evidence collected during the course of the preliminary inquiry or investigation.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (10846)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Removal and suspension of Chairperson and Members of Lokpal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10846&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Lokpal shall not`
  line `inquire into any complaint made against the Chairperson or any Member.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (4), the Chairperson or any Member shall be removed`
  line `from his office by order of the President on grounds of misbehaviour after the Supreme Court, on a`
  line `reference being made to it by the President on a petition signed by at least one hundred Members of`
  line `Parliament has, on an inquiry held in accordance with the procedure prescribed in that behalf, reported`
  line `that the Chairperson or such Member, as the case may be, ought to be removed on such ground.`
  line
  line `(3) The President may suspend from office the Chairperson or any Member in respect of whom a`
  line `reference has been made to the Supreme Court under sub-section (2), on receipt of the recommendation or`
  line `interim order made by the Supreme Court in this regard until the President has passed orders on receipt of`
  line `the final report of the Supreme Court on such reference.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the President may, by order, remove from`
  line `the office, the Chairperson or any Member if the Chairperson or such Member, as the case may be,—`
  line
  line `(a) is adjudged an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) engages, during his term of office, in any paid employment outside the duties of his office; or`
  line
  line `(c) is, in the opinion of the President, unfit to continue in office by reason of infirmity of mind or`
  line body.
  line
  line `(5) If the Chairperson or any Member is, or becomes, in any way concerned or interested in any`
  line `contract or agreement made by or on behalf of the Government of India or the Government of a State or`
  line `participates in any way in the profit thereof or in any benefit or emolument arising therefrom otherwise`
  line `than as a member and in common with the other members of an incorporated company, he shall, for the`
  line `purposes of sub-section (2), be deemed to be guilty of misbehaviour.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (10847)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Complaints against officials of Lokpal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10847&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every complaint of allegation or wrongdoing made`
  line `against any officer or employee or agency (including the Delhi Special Police Establishment), under or`
  line `associated with the Lokpal for an offence punishable under the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988`
  line `(49 of 1988) shall be dealt with in accordance with the provisions of this section.`
  line
  line `(2) The Lokpal shall complete the inquiry into the complaint or allegation made within a period of`
  line `thirty days from the date of its receipt.`
  line
  line `(3) While making an inquiry into the complaint against any officer or employee of the Lokpal or`
  line `agency engaged or associated with the Lokpal, if it is prima facie satisfied on the basis of evidence`
  line `available, that—`
  line
  line `(a) continuance of such officer or employee of the Lokpal or agency engaged or associated in his`
  line `post while conducting the inquiry is likely to affect such inquiry adversely; or`
  line
  line `(b) an officer or employee of the Lokpal or agency engaged or associated is likely to destroy or in`
  line `any way tamper with the evidence or influence witnesses,`
  line
  line `then, the Lokpal may, by order, suspend such officer or employee of the Lokpal or divest such agency`
  line `engaged or associated with the Lokpal of all powers and responsibilities hereto before exercised by it.`
  line
  line `(4) On the completion of the inquiry, if the Lokpal is satisfied that there is prima facie evidence of the`
  line `commission of an offence under the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988 (49 of 1988) or of any`
  line `wrongdoing, it shall, within a period of fifteen days of the completion of such inquiry, order to prosecute`
  line `such officer or employee of the Lokpal or such officer, employee, agency engaged or associated with the`
  line `Lokpal and initiate disciplinary proceedings against the official concerned:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be passed without giving such officer or employee of the Lokpal,`
  line `such officer, employee, agency engaged or associated, a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (10848)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Assessment of loss and recovery thereof by special court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10848&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `If any public servant is convicted`
  line `of an offence under the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988 (49 of 1988) by the special Court,`
  line `notwithstanding and without prejudice to any law for the time being in force, it may make an assessment`
  line `of loss, if any, caused to the public exchequer on account of the actions or decisions of such public`
  line `servant not taken in good faith and for which he stands convicted, and may order recovery of such loss, if`
  line `possible or quantifiable, from such public servant so convicted:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Special Court, for reasons to be recorded in writing, comes to the conclusion that`
  line `the loss caused was pursuant to a conspiracy with the beneficiary or beneficiaries of actions or decisions`
  line `of the public servant so convicted, then such loss may, if assessed and quantifiable under this section, also`
  line `be recovered from such beneficiary or beneficiaries proportionately.`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (10849)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title Budget.
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10849&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `The Lokpal shall prepare, in such form and at such time in each financial year as may`
  line `be prescribed, its budget for the next financial year, showing the estimated receipts and expenditure of the`
  line `Lokpal and forward the same to the Central Government for information.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (10850)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Grants by Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10850&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due appropriation made`
  line `by Parliament by law in this behalf, make to the Lokpal grants of such sums of money as are required to`
  line `be paid for the salaries and allowances payable to the Chairperson and Members and the administrative`
  line `expenses, including the salaries and allowances and pension payable to or in respect of officers and other`
  line `employees of the Lokpal.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (10851)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Annual statement of accounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10851&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Lokpal shall maintain proper accounts and other`
  line `relevant records and prepare an annual statement of accounts in such form as may be prescribed by the`
  line `Central Government in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India.`
  line
  line `(2) The accounts of the Lokpal shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India at`
  line `such intervals as may be specified by him.`
  line
  line `(3) The Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any person appointed by him in connection with`
  line `the audit of the accounts of the Lokpal under this Act shall have the same rights, privileges and authority`
  line `in connection with such audit, as the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India generally has, in`
  line `connection with the audit of the Government accounts and, in particular, shall have the right to demand`
  line `the production of books, accounts, connected vouchers and other documents and papers and to inspect`
  line `any of the offices of the Lokpal.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Lokpal, as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or any`
  line `other person appointed by him in this behalf, together with the audit report thereon, shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and the Central Government shall cause the same to be laid before`
  line `each House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (10852)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Furnishing of returns, etc., to Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10852&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `The Lokpal shall furnish to the Central`
  line `Government, at such time and in such form and manner as may be prescribed or as the Central`
  line `Government may request, such returns and statements and such particulars in regard to any matter under`
  line `the jurisdiction of the Lokpal, as the Central Government may, from time to time, require.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (10853)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Declaration of assets.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 37 of 2016, s. 2, for section 44 (w.e.f. 16-1-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10853&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[44. Declaration of assets.—On and from the date of commencement of this Act, every public`
  line `servant shall make a declaration of his assets and liabilities in such form and manner as may be`
  line prescribed.]
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (10854)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Presumption as to acquisition of assets by corrupt means in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10854&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `If any public`
  line `servant wilfully or for reasons which are not justifiable, fails to—`
  line
  line `(a) to declare his assets; or`
  line
  line `(b) gives misleading information in respect of such assets and is found to be in possession of`
  line `assets not disclosed or in respect of which misleading information was furnished,`
  line
  line `then, such assets shall, unless otherwise proved, be presumed to belong to the public servant and shall be`
  line `presumed to be assets acquired by corrupt means:`
  line
  line `Provided that the competent authority may condone or exempt the public servant from furnishing`
  line `information in respect of assets not exceeding such minimum value as may be prescribed`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (10855)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Prosecution for false complaint and payment of compensation, etc., to public servant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10855&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `(1)`
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, whoever makes any false and frivolous or vexatious`
  line `complaint under this Act shall, on conviction, be punished with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to one year and with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees.`
  line
  line `(2) No Court, except a Special Court, shall take cognizance of an offence under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) No Special Court shall take cognizance of an offence under sub-section (1) except on a complaint`
  line `made by a person against whom the false, frivolous or vexatious complaint was made or by an officer`
  line `authorised by the Lokpal.`
  line
  line `(4) The prosecution in relation to an offence under sub-section (1) shall be conducted by the public`
  line `prosecutor and all expenses connected with such prosecution shall be borne by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) In case of conviction of a person [being an individual or society or association of persons or trust`
  line `(whether registered or not)], for having made a false complaint under this Act, such person shall be liable`
  line `to pay compensation to the public servant against whom he made the false complaint in addition to the`
  line `legal expenses for contesting the case by such public servant, as the Special Court may determine.`
  line
  line `(6) Nothing contained in this section shall apply in case of complaints made in good faith.`
  line
  line `Explanation.—For the purpose of this sub-section, the expression "good faith" means any act`
  line `believed or done by a person in good faith with due care, caution and sense of responsibility or by mistake`
  line `of fact believing himself justified by law under section 79 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (10856)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `False complaint made by society or association of persons or trust.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10856&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any offence`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 46 has been committed by any society or association of persons or trust`
  line `(whether registered or not), every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was directly in`
  line `charge of, and was responsible to, the society or association of persons or trust, for the conduct of the`
  line `business or affairs or activities of the society or association of persons or trust as well as such society or`
  line `association of persons or trust shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be`
  line `proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he had exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a society or association of persons or trust (whether registered or not) and it is proved that`
  line `the offence has been committed with the consent or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the`
  line `part of, any director, manager, secretary or other officer of such society or association of persons or trust,`
  line `such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and`
  line `shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (10857)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Reports of Lokpal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10857&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of the Lokpal to present annually to the President a`
  line `report on the work done by the Lokpal and on receipt of such report the President shall cause a copy`
  line `thereof together with a memorandum explaining, in respect of the cases, if any, where the advice of the`
  line `Lokpal was not accepted, the reason for such non-acceptance to be laid before each House of Parliament`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (10858)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Lokpal to function as appellate authority for appeals arising out of any other law for the time being in force.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10858&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `The Lokpal shall function as the final appellate authority in respect of appeals`
  line `arising out of any other law for the time being in force providing for delivery of public services and`
  line `redressal of public grievances by any public authority in cases where the decision contains findings of`
  line `corruption under the Prevention of Corruption Act, 1988 (49 of 1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (10859)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith by any public servant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10859&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other`
  line `legal proceedings under this Act shall lie against any public servant, in respect of anything which is done`
  line `in good faith or intended to be done in the discharge of his official functions or in exercise of his powers.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (10860)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith by others.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10860&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal`
  line `proceedings shall lie against the Lokpal or against any officer, employee, agency or any person, in respect`
  line `of anything which is done in good faith or intended to be done under this Act or the rules or the`
  line `regulations made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (10861)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Members, officers and employees of Lokpal to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10861&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson,`
  line `Members, officers and other employees of the Lokpal shall be deemed, when acting or purporting to act`
  line `in pursuance of any of the provisions of this Act, to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of`
  line `the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (10862)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Limitation to apply in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10862&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `The Lokpal shall not inquire or investigate into any`
  line `complaint, if the complaint is made after the expiry of a period of seven years from the date on which the`
  line `offence mentioned in such complaint is alleged to have been committed.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (10863)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Bar of jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10863&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction in respect of any matter which the`
  line `Lokpal is empowered by or under this Act to determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (10864)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Legal assistance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10864&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `The Lokpal shall provide to every person against whom a complaint has been`
  line `made, before it, under this Act, legal assistance to defend his case before the Lokpal, if such assistance is`
  line `requested for.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (10865)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10865&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent therewith contained in any enactment other than this Act or in any instrument`
  line `having effect by virtue of any enactment other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (10866)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Provisions of this Act to be in addition of other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10866&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall be in`
  line `addition to, and not in derogation of, any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_58:
  sectionId (10867)
  sectionNo (58)
  orderNo 58
  title `Amendment of certain enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_58_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10867&sectionno=58&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_58_content:
  string
  line `The enactments specified in the Schedule shall be`
  line `amended in the manner specified therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_58_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_59:
  sectionId (10868)
  sectionNo (59)
  orderNo 59
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_59_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 37 of 2016. s. 3, for clause (k) (w.e.f. 16-1-2014)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10868&sectionno=59&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_59_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the form of complaint referred to in clause (e) of sub-section (1) of section 2;`
  line
  line `(b) the term of the Search Committee, the fee and allowances payable to its members and the`
  line `manner of selection of panel of names under sub-section (5) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) the post or posts in respect of which the appointment shall be made after consultation with the`
  line `Union Public Service Commission under the proviso to sub-section (3) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(d) other matters for which the Lokpal shall have the powers of a civil court under clause (vi) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 27;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner of sending the order of attachment along with the material to the Special Court`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 29;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner of transmitting the letter of request under sub-section (2) of section 36;`
  line
  line `(g) the form and the time for preparing in each financial year the budget for the next financial`
  line `year, showing the estimated receipts and expenditure of the Lokpal under section 40;`
  line
  line `(h) the form for maintaining the accounts and other relevant records and the form of annual`
  line `statement of accounts under sub-section (1) of section 42;`
  line
  line `(i) the form and manner and the time for preparing the returns and statements along with`
  line `particulars under section 43;`
  line
  line `(j) the form and the time for preparing an annual return giving a summary of its activities during`
  line `the previous year under sub-section (5) of section 44;`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(k) the form and manner of declaration of assets and liabilities by public servants under`
  line `section 44:`
  line
  line `Provided that the rules may be made under this clause retrospectively from the date on which that`
  line `provisions of this Act came into force;]`
  line
  line `(l) the minimum value for which the competent authority may condone or exempt a public`
  line `servant from furnishing information in respect of assets under the proviso to section 45;`
  line
  line `(m) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_60:
  sectionId (10869)
  sectionNo (60)
  orderNo 60
  title `Power of Lokpal to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_60_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10869&sectionno=60&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_60_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act and the rules`
  line `made thereunder, the Lokpal may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make regulations to carry out`
  line `the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) the conditions of service of the secretary and other officers and staff of the Lokpal and the`
  line `matters which in so far as they relate to salaries, allowances, leave or pensions, require the approval`
  line `of the President under sub-section (4) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(b) the place of sittings of benches of the Lokpal under clause (f) of sub-section (1) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner for displaying on the website of the Lokpal, the status of all complaints pending or`
  line `disposed of along with records and evidence with reference thereto under sub-section (10) of`
  line `section 20;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner and procedure of conducting preliminary inquiry or investigation under`
  line `sub-section (11) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, specified under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_60_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_61:
  sectionId (10870)
  sectionNo (61)
  orderNo 61
  title `Laying of rules and regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_61_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10870&sectionno=61&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_61_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and regulation made under this Act shall be laid,`
  line `as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total`
  line `period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and`
  line `if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid,`
  line `both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation, or both Houses agree that the rule`
  line `or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such modified`
  line `form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be`
  line `without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_61_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_62:
  sectionId (10871)
  sectionNo (62)
  orderNo 62
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_62_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10871&sectionno=62&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_62_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, as appear to be necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of a period of two years`
  line `from the commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_62_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_63:
  sectionId (10872)
  sectionNo (63)
  orderNo 63
  title `Establishment of Lokayukta.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_63_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889&sectionId=10872&sectionno=63&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_26_36_00014_201401_1517807327889
obj_root_law_sections_63_content:
  string
  line `Every State shall establish a body to be known as the Lokayukta`
  line `for the State, if not so established, constituted or appointed, by a law made by the State Legislature, to`
  line `deal with complaints relating to corruption against certain public functionaries, within a period of one`
  line `year from the date of commencement of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_63_footnotes:
  string
  line
